  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.7872" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>London<lb/> 64, St. George’s Square,<lb/> 28/6/83 S. W. </dateline>
        <opener>Dear Sir/ </opener>
        <p>Your letter of June 9: If you require Goldie, Efik Dictionary,<note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.7540">Rev. Hugh Goldie, <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Dictionary of the Efik language</hi>, Edinburgh: United Presbyterian College Buildings, [1870].</ref>
            </bibl>
          </note> write to <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2252">Friederich Muller</persName>,<note n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2252">Friedrich Müller</persName> (1854-1898), österr. Linguist u. Ethnograph; vgl. HSA 07571-07585. – Im Sinne von: „vielleicht haben Sie Dr. F. Müller schon befragt“?</note> and bow his copy: he has the book; if this does not succeed – write to Dr R Rost – India Office: Westminster<note
            n="3" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2561">Reinhold Rost</persName> (1822-1896), Bibliothekar u. Orientalist; vgl. HSA 09722-09797.</note> – he promises to lend you his copy</p>
        <p>Write a letter in English to Archdeacon Dandeson Crowther,<note n="4" place="foot" type="editorial">

            <persName>
Dandeson Crowther</persName> (1844-1938), Archdeacon of the The Niger from 1876-1926; Sohn von <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1340">Samuel Ajayi Crowther</persName>, vgl. 
HSA 02036 (von <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.1600">Wolf, Nachlaß</ref>

            </bibl>, 15 fälschlich dem Vater, Bischof Samuel Ajayi Crowther zugewiesen.</note> son of the Bishop, who is now in England – his address is Church Mission Home <pb
            facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> Salisbury Square London: he will reply – the dd<note n="5" place="foot" type="editorial">Divinitatis Doctor?</note> Bishop has no time.</p>
        <p>Kohler, book on Bonny Sprache (Gottingen) is not worth having. I have a copy I have small Primers or Vocabularies of </p>
        <p>Idzo } all on</p>
        <p>Ibo } the</p>
        <p>Igaza } Lower</p>
        <p>Igbira } Niger</p>

        <p>I could lend them to you if you will wait till my Book is out – it will be published in September, and will tell <pb
            facs="#IMG.3" n="3"/> you a great deal</p>
        <p>Nothing has been published about the Calabar Languages except Goldie’s Books<note n="6" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.7541">Hugh Goldie, <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Calabar and its mission</hi>, Edinburgh [u.a.]: Oliphant Anderson &amp;amp; Ferrier, 1890</ref>
            </bibl>; <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.7542">Ders., <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Memoir of King Ëyo VII of Old Calabar. A Christian King of Africa</hi>, Edinburgh 1894.</ref>
            </bibl>
          </note> – I know nothing about the Neger gehein Sprachen,<note n="7" place="foot" type="editorial">Vgl. <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.545">
Schuchardt, „[Rez. von:] Coelho, F. Adolpho, Os dialectos romanicos ou neo-latinos na Africa, Asia e America. Notas complementares“, Literaturblatt für germanische und romanische Philologie 4, 1883, 279-282</ref>

            </bibl>, Sp. 282: „Die (auf afri¬kanischer Grundlage ruhende) Geheimsprache der ‘ñáñigos’ werde ich zum Gegenstand einer besonderen Untersuchung machen“.</note> to which you allude, nor have I seen Dr Bartrams<note
            n="8" place="foot" type="editorial">Nicht identifiziert, oder sollte es sich um den Naturforscher William Bartram (1739-1823) handeln?</note> article on that subject. </p>
        <p>The Bishops of Calcutta and Bombay would not reply to letters on such subjects – they are too busy</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours faithfully</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1346">Robert Cust</persName>
            <lb/> T.O.<note n="9" place="foot" type="editorial">„Turn Over“.</note>
          </signed>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.4" n="4"/>
        <postscript>
          <p>Of course you have Koelles Polyglotta africána<note n="10" place="foot" type="editorial">
              <bibl>
                <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.7543">
Sigismund Wilhelm Koelle, <hi
                    rend="unknown" rendition="#none">
Polyglotta africana or a comparative vocabulary of nearly three hundred words and phrases in more than one hundred distinct African languages</hi>, London: Church Missionary House, 1854.</ref>
              </bibl>
            </note>
          </p>
        </postscript>
      </div>
